******
[1] Cholera - Congo DR (Katanga Province)
Date: Sat 20 Dec 2014
Source: Radio Okapi [in French, machine trans., edited]
http://radiookapi.net/actualite/2014/12/20/kalemie-20-cas-de-cholera-enregistres-tembwe-1-mort/


A total of 20 cases of cholera, including 1 death, have been recorded in the locality of Tembwe, 90 km [56 mi] south east of Kalemie (Katanga). The health area registered nurse, Norbert Tambwe, who provided this information on Sat 20 Dec 2014, said the victims have been identified over 2 months. According to him, the population of Tembwe is exposed to cholera because of its proximity to the waters of Lake Tanganyika. "The village of Tembwe is on the edge of the lake and the entire population, its activities, are at the lake. Above all, the population does not respect hygienic measures, despite the education and the lessons that we give them," said Norbert Tambwe Masudi.

