******
[2] Cholera - Congo DR (Katanga Province)
Date: Thu 18 Dec 2014
Source: Radio Okapi [in French, machine trans., edited]
http://radiookapi.net/actualite/2014/12/18/katanga-249-personnes-sont-mortes-de-cholera-depuis-janvier-selon-ocha/


Between 1 Jan 2014 and 7 Dec 2014, 249 people died of cholera, among the 8700 cases registered in the province of Katanga. The Office for the Coordination of Humanitarian Affairs (OCHA) delivered these figures in its bulletin, published on Wed 17 Dec 2014, in Lubumbashi. Between 1 Jan 2013 and 10 Dec 2013, OCHA had registered in the same province 12 600 cholera cases including 302 deaths.

For OCHA, these many cases of cholera have been notably listed in 2014 in Fungurume, Likasi, Kolwezi, and Lubumbashi. This situation is due to the delay in the delivery of means to support the sick and the difficulty of access to these areas. Of the 68 health areas in the province, notes the humanitarian agency, 34 are affected by cholera.

